+
+## 5. What Hermes should ask the owner to approve next
+
+1. Ask for owner priority confirmation on internal routing: Deep Read `EXP-20260630-005`, Deep Read or Fast Kill `EXP-20260630-006`, Fast Kill `GOV-20260630-004`, Deep Read after quick Fast Kill `GOV-20260630-003`, Fast Kill `GOV-20260630-006` and `GOV-20260630-005`, and reject/park `GOV-20260630-007`. This is internal analysis only and uses `data/master_cases.csv`, `outputs/source_scans/export_rfq_batch_scan_20260630_131453.md`, and `outputs/source_scans/gov_radar_batch_20260630131554.md`.
+2. Ask the owner whether credentialed access should be approved for UNDP Quantum and TradeKey verification after internal Fast Kill. Do not register, log in, message, bid, or submit without a separate approval card. Evidence: `outputs/source_scans/export_rfq_batch_scan_20260630_131453.md`; `config/sources.export.yaml`.
+3. Ask the owner to Ask Changes on `APR-001` for `EXP-20260630-002` until original RFQ URL, buyer legal identity, buyer message/document/screenshot, concrete risk, recovery path, and a second quote proof are captured. Evidence: `outputs/case_reports/EXP-20260630-002/rfq_evidence_intake_EXP-20260630-002.md`; `data/approvals_receipts.csv`.
+4. Ask the owner to approve or reject `APR-002` and `APR-003` only if they want supplier quote requests for older cases `GOV-20260630-001` and `EXP-20260630-001`; those are separate from today's top fresh demand signals and remain approval-gated. Evidence: `data/approvals_receipts.csv`; `data/agent_run_log.csv`; `outputs/case_reports/EXP-20260630-001/audit_EXP-20260630-001.md`.
+
+## 6. Safety line
+
+No external business action executed: no supplier/buyer messages, no tender/RFQ submission or portal upload, no login/CAPTCHA/paywall bypass, no payment/EMD/security deposit/advance/DSC use, and no final HSN/ITC-HS classification, origin claim, price, delivery, or payment-term commitment. Evidence: `data/agent_run_log.csv`; `outputs/source_scans/export_rfq_batch_scan_20260630_131453.md`; `outputs/source_scans/gov_radar_batch_20260630131554.md`.

